cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with personalized speech recognition and language modeling. It may also fall under "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) as it uses social networks for crowdsourcing user characteristic features. "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) is another possible category as the paper proposes a recurrent neural network language model. "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR) and "Sound" (cs.SD) are also possible categories as the paper deals with speech recognition and acoustic models.
